\frac{1}{n}+\frac{1}{n+1}+......+\frac{1}{n+2n}
\sum_{i = 0}^{2n} \frac{1}{n + i} = \sum_{i = 0}^{2n} \frac 1 n \cdot \frac 1 {1 + i/n} = \sum_{i =0}^{2n} \frac 1 n f\left(\frac i n\right)
f(x) = \frac 1 {1 + x}
y=1/x
\int_k^{k+1} \frac{dx}{x} \lt \frac{1}{k}\lt \int_{k-1}^k \frac{dx}{x}.
\int_n^{3n}\frac{dx}{x}\lt \sum_n^{3n}\frac{1}{k}\lt \int_{n-1}^{3n-1} \frac{dx}{x}.
